summary: An Ordinance accepting a deed, executed on the 9th day of July, A. D., 1896, by the Danville Coal Company, by R. L. Thorne, its president, to the City of Seattle, for a perpetual right of way 66 feet wide, for pipe lines, wagon road, telphone lines, etc., over and across Lot 12, Section 24, Township 22 North, Range 6 East of W. M., in King County, Washington.
